@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{bbdb-extras.el} extends BBDB (the Insidious Big Brother Database),
Emacs' contact management system.  The stock BBDB interface requires
several prompts to create a record and asks for confirmation before
routine actions such as opening a URL or deleting a field.  This
package streamlines those interactions and adds the ability to export
contacts to the system address book.

The extensions fall into three areas:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Quick record creation}: create a new contact by providing only a
name, skipping the prompts for email, phone, and other fields
(@ref{Quick record creation}).
@item
@strong{Export}: send the current BBDB record to macOS Contacts as a vCard
(@ref{Exporting to vCard}).
@item
@strong{Patched behaviors}: open URLs without confirmation and display the
BBDB buffer without splitting windows (@ref{Patched functions}).
@end itemize

