@node Quick record creation
@section Quick record creation

@findex bbdb-extras-create-quick
When you just need to jot down someone's name without filling in every
field, use @code{bbdb-extras-create-quick}.  It prompts only for the
contact's first and last name, creates a minimal BBDB record, and
displays it.  This replaces the standard @code{bbdb-create-internal}
workflow, which asks for email, phone, address, and notes.

Internally the command delegates to @code{bbdb-extras-read-record-quick}
(@ref{Reading a quick record}), which handles the name prompt and
validation.

@node Exporting to vCard
@section Exporting to vCard

@findex bbdb-extras-export-vcard
The command @code{bbdb-extras-export-vcard} exports the BBDB record at
point to a temporary @samp{.vcf} file and opens it with the system's
default handler (@samp{open} on macOS), which is typically the Contacts
application.  This provides a quick path from BBDB to the system
address book without manual copy-pasting.  It relies on the
@samp{bbdb-vcard} package for the actual vCard serialization.

@node Deleting without confirmation
@section Deleting without confirmation

@findex bbdb-extras-delete-field-or-record-no-confirm
By default, @code{bbdb-delete-field-or-record} asks for confirmation before
every deletion.  If you find this disruptive---especially during bulk
cleanup---the command
@code{bbdb-extras-delete-field-or-record-no-confirm} performs the same
deletion but bypasses the confirmation prompt.  Use with care, as the
action is not undoable.

