@chapter Functions

@menu
* Reading a quick record::
@end menu

@node Reading a quick record
@section Reading a quick record

@findex bbdb-extras-read-record-quick
The function @code{bbdb-extras-read-record-quick} creates an empty BBDB
record and populates only its first and last name fields via
@code{bbdb-read-name}.  The optional FIRST-AND-LAST argument controls the
reading mode (see the @code{bbdb-read-name} docstring for details).  This
function is used by @code{bbdb-extras-create-quick}
(@ref{Quick record creation}).

@node Patched functions
@chapter Patched functions

@samp{bbdb-extras.el} overrides two standard BBDB functions via @code{advice-add}
with @samp{:override}.

@menu
* Browsing URLs directly::
* Displaying the BBDB buffer::
@end menu

@node Browsing URLs directly
@section Browsing URLs directly

@findex bbdb-extras-browse-url
The function @code{bbdb-extras-browse-url} replaces @code{bbdb-browse-url}.  The
stock version asks the user to confirm before opening each URL; the
patched version opens the URL in the @samp{url} field directly with
@code{browse-url}.  A prefix argument WHICH (starting from 0) selects which
URL to open when the field contains multiple entries.

@node Displaying the BBDB buffer
@section Displaying the BBDB buffer

@findex bbdb-extras-pop-up-window
The function @code{bbdb-extras-pop-up-window} replaces @code{bbdb-pop-up-window}.
The stock version splits the largest window to show the @samp{*BBDB*}
buffer, which can be disruptive in tiled layouts.  The patched version
reuses an existing window instead of splitting, providing a less
intrusive display.  If the @samp{*BBDB*} buffer is already visible, the
function simply selects its window when SELECT is non-nil.

